WEBVTT

00:01:45.371 --> 00:01:46.239
Confirmed.

00:01:49.342 --> 00:01:52.312
To our new relationship,
and our new friendship.

00:01:52.378 --> 00:01:54.814
And to prosperity.

00:01:55.548 --> 00:01:58.318
The view from here makes me sad
that I must leave so soon.

00:01:58.384 --> 00:02:01.121
It's an amazing sight.

00:02:01.187 --> 00:02:03.323
Next time, we should have dinner together.

00:02:04.357 --> 00:02:07.193
The Cantonese cuisine
that our head chef makes

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:10.330
is just about as superb
as this scenery.

00:02:10.396 --> 00:02:12.699
That's a wonderful invitation, however...

00:02:13.833 --> 00:02:17.604
to think that the day that I'd dine with
an executive from the Red Dragon...

00:02:18.171 --> 00:02:21.741
Rest assured,
the food will not be poisoned.

00:02:31.784 --> 00:02:34.287
I can finally take a breather.

00:02:34.354 --> 00:02:35.622
Thank God.

00:02:52.539 --> 00:02:55.441
Doing things like this
won't do you any good.

00:02:56.743 --> 00:02:58.778
Times have changed.

00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:02.382
The syndicate cannot survive
just by fighting alone.

00:03:06.786 --> 00:03:10.490
Only if Spike returned

00:03:11.424 --> 00:03:13.293
someone like you would...

00:03:28.241 --> 00:03:30.376
I don't feel up for this.

00:03:32.345 --> 00:03:33.212
What?

00:03:33.546 --> 00:03:35.615
I said, I don't feel like doing this.

00:03:36.416 --> 00:03:37.684
Then there's no choice.

00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:39.819
Wait, Spike.

00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:41.321
I can't burden you.

00:03:41.754 --> 00:03:43.356
Don't say stuff like that.

00:03:43.890 --> 00:03:45.525
You know who that is, don't you?

00:03:45.992 --> 00:03:48.294
-Superficial stuff, yeah.
-Then...

00:03:48.595 --> 00:03:51.464
Good money.
Easy to get info on him.

00:03:51.531 --> 00:03:52.699
We also have a lead.

00:03:53.299 --> 00:03:54.701
What makes you scared?

00:03:55.768 --> 00:03:58.972
Spike, you're deliberately
avoiding the subject.

00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.807
Are you hiding something from me?

00:04:02.275 --> 00:04:03.910
So, what happened
to that arm of yours?

00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:07.680
-What does that have to do with anything?
-Nothing.

00:04:07.914 --> 00:04:10.350
So, you have no intention of telling me?

00:04:10.683 --> 00:04:11.818
I could ask you the same.

00:04:17.557 --> 00:04:19.826
Why is this door so damn narrow?

00:04:24.497 --> 00:04:26.833
-Am I interrupting something?
-None of your business.

00:04:26.899 --> 00:04:29.902
We're supposed to be comrades.
That's awfully cold of you.

00:04:29.969 --> 00:04:31.604
What do you mean, comrades?

00:04:31.671 --> 00:04:34.040
Troublemakers should keep
themselves out of this.

00:04:35.275 --> 00:04:36.843
Well, I don't care.

00:04:39.579 --> 00:04:42.715
-So, who is this? What's he up to?
-Don't look without asking us.

00:04:42.782 --> 00:04:45.585
What do you mean?
He's just there on the screen.

00:04:45.985 --> 00:04:46.953
Spike.

00:04:47.487 --> 00:04:48.755
Hey, wait, Spike.

00:05:00.333 --> 00:05:02.502
-I'm taking off.
<i>-Spike.</i>

00:05:02.568 --> 00:05:05.405
<i>-Shit, I won't be responsible for you.</i>
-Roger that.

00:05:12.345 --> 00:05:14.447
Damn it. He's such a...

00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:16.582
"Mao Yenrai.

00:05:16.649 --> 00:05:19.585
A bounty of 28 million
for the alleged murder

00:05:19.652 --> 00:05:21.888
of an executive from
an opposing syndicate."

00:05:21.954 --> 00:05:24.424
Amazing. And you guys are after him?

00:05:26.092 --> 00:05:27.827
What, did you have a fight?

00:05:28.094 --> 00:05:29.729
Shut up. You're being obnoxious.

00:05:31.097 --> 00:05:33.599
-You're such a kid.
-I said, you're being obnoxious!

00:05:34.567 --> 00:05:36.436
He can do whatever the hell he pleases.

00:05:37.570 --> 00:05:39.839
Oh, God.
He's throwing such a huge fit.

00:05:43.976 --> 00:05:46.112
<i>You there, Jet?</i>
<i>I got something big for you.</i>

00:05:46.813 --> 00:05:48.081
Something big?

00:06:06.833 --> 00:06:11.104
Excuse me, madam,
but I need to see your ticket.

00:06:11.370 --> 00:06:13.873
Oh, I don't have anything like that.

00:06:14.073 --> 00:06:17.410
Well, then, I am afraid
that you cannot enter the hall.

00:06:17.477 --> 00:06:20.747
But they told me I didn't need one.

00:06:21.380 --> 00:06:23.916
You know. The guy in the box seat.

00:06:24.717 --> 00:06:25.985
Him.

00:06:26.052 --> 00:06:27.553
Mao Yenr--

00:06:29.155 --> 00:06:31.524
Can you park my vehicle for me?

00:06:36.095 --> 00:06:37.797
If it's not one, it's the other.

00:06:37.864 --> 00:06:39.999
Why do they all do everything
as they please?

00:06:42.535 --> 00:06:44.604
{\an8}There's a protective encryption
on this thing.

00:06:47.173 --> 00:06:48.608
You worried?

00:06:48.674 --> 00:06:51.711
Just watch.
These are decrypted like this

00:06:53.112 --> 00:06:56.916
{\an8}See? And then, I input "Mao Yenrai."

00:06:59.485 --> 00:07:02.889
The bounty part
sure seems to be true, but...

00:07:46.732 --> 00:07:48.901
Is this Sir Mao's seat?

00:07:48.968 --> 00:07:51.237
I looked all over for it.
Actually, I...

00:07:51.838 --> 00:07:53.539
We were waiting for you.

00:07:57.777 --> 00:08:00.780
They are performing,
so please stay quiet.

00:08:20.132 --> 00:08:21.234
Hold it right there!

00:08:26.539 --> 00:08:27.840
I'm not letting you get away.

00:08:32.245 --> 00:08:33.279
What are you doing?!

00:08:37.149 --> 00:08:39.652
Give it back.
Shit. Give it back, you dumbass!

00:08:42.555 --> 00:08:44.557
Really, kids these days.

00:08:44.957 --> 00:08:47.026
I'll hand you over to the cops.

00:08:49.795 --> 00:08:50.663
You.

00:08:58.738 --> 00:09:01.807
Hey, isn't it bad for you
to drink it in one shot, Annie?

00:09:02.308 --> 00:09:06.579
You coming back to life
is worse on me than this glass.

00:09:06.979 --> 00:09:08.581
What terrible treatment.

00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:11.584
The words of the dead are meaningless.

00:09:11.651 --> 00:09:12.952
But I'm alive.

00:09:13.553 --> 00:09:17.557
No, you died three years ago.
That's how things work here.

00:09:26.132 --> 00:09:27.300
I know.

00:09:29.168 --> 00:09:32.805
The fact that you came here means you
have something you want to know, right?

00:09:33.105 --> 00:09:35.107
If it's not much, I can be of help.

00:09:36.976 --> 00:09:37.910
Anastasia.

00:09:38.244 --> 00:09:42.348
Stop it. There are only two people
that can call me by that name.

00:09:44.717 --> 00:09:46.786
So, what do you want to know?

00:09:47.219 --> 00:09:48.354
Mao Yenrai.

00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:51.591
What happened to him?

00:10:02.969 --> 00:10:05.972
Mao-taijin?
There's a reason for this.

00:10:06.372 --> 00:10:09.008
No need to talk, Ms. Valentine.

00:10:10.276 --> 00:10:12.745
We have done
a background check already.

00:10:13.946 --> 00:10:17.216
Rest assured, it will be held
in a safe location.

00:10:17.817 --> 00:10:19.218
Please, to your seat.

00:10:41.340 --> 00:10:42.408
You're trembling.

00:10:44.343 --> 00:10:46.278
Who are you?

00:10:49.415 --> 00:10:50.316
Vicious.

00:11:12.838 --> 00:11:13.706
You know...

00:11:15.074 --> 00:11:16.675
I won't say anything bad to you.

00:11:16.976 --> 00:11:19.345
Don't get yourself involved
with Vicious anymore.

00:11:20.713 --> 00:11:22.181
But I know saying that is useless.

00:11:23.015 --> 00:11:23.983
Sorry.

00:11:24.717 --> 00:11:27.386
You've never listened
to what others say.

00:11:31.924 --> 00:11:34.126
On top of it,
you're a stubborn showoff.

00:11:34.193 --> 00:11:37.930
It can't hurt you to listen to
your elders once in a while.

00:11:40.232 --> 00:11:41.300
About Mao...

00:11:42.468 --> 00:11:46.806
he had a lot of people looking
for you after you were gone.

00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:49.942
He said that you still had to be alive.

00:11:51.243 --> 00:11:55.314
You're finally back, but Mao is...

00:11:56.882 --> 00:11:58.084
Stop it already.

00:11:58.150 --> 00:11:59.885
This is for Mao.

00:12:02.288 --> 00:12:04.323
I'll take that one for Mao.

00:12:27.012 --> 00:12:29.815
What are you up to now
to need something like that?

00:12:30.883 --> 00:12:31.884
Where's the broad?

00:12:32.284 --> 00:12:35.287
She lost sanity looking at
the bounty figure and took off.

00:12:35.521 --> 00:12:38.357
Right now she's probably
somewhere, screwing up.

00:12:38.924 --> 00:12:39.792
I see.

00:12:40.493 --> 00:12:43.863
I'll tell you something.
You won't get the bounty for Mao.

00:12:44.430 --> 00:12:46.465
He's already dead. He was killed.

00:12:47.233 --> 00:12:50.336
Internal discord.
Do you understand?

00:12:50.402 --> 00:12:52.238
This is a trap. I'm sure of it.

00:12:52.805 --> 00:12:54.940
Yeah. I know all that.

00:12:55.374 --> 00:12:57.009
You know?

00:12:58.410 --> 00:13:00.212
Then what, you're Mao's?

00:13:01.046 --> 00:13:02.214
I owe him one from before.

00:13:06.418 --> 00:13:08.187
I'll tell you something, Spike.

00:13:09.889 --> 00:13:12.892
This arm. It's the price I paid
for being over-spirited

00:13:12.958 --> 00:13:15.361
and running ahead of the game.
You understand?

00:13:15.895 --> 00:13:17.296
I don't wanna go, either.

00:13:17.496 --> 00:13:18.364
Then...

00:13:19.431 --> 00:13:21.534
Let's just say,
duties of the life I live.

00:13:28.374 --> 00:13:29.975
<i>I've been caught.</i>

00:13:30.042 --> 00:13:31.110
You...

00:13:31.410 --> 00:13:33.345
<i>Come to the place we specify.</i>

00:13:33.946 --> 00:13:37.183
<i>Otherwise, my life is over.</i>
<i>So they say,</i>

00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:39.351
<i>Lesse... the time to meet is...</i>

00:13:39.418 --> 00:13:41.120
It's because you did as you please.

00:13:41.187 --> 00:13:44.056
<i>You're being cold.</i>
<i>We're comrades, remember?</i>

00:13:44.857 --> 00:13:48.027
You reap what you sow.
Take care of it all yourself.

00:13:48.093 --> 00:13:48.994
<i>Hey, wait.</i>

00:13:50.262 --> 00:13:51.363
Where is it?

00:13:52.464 --> 00:13:53.899
<i>You're really gonna come?</i>

00:13:54.934 --> 00:13:57.937
Don't worry.
I'm not going there to save you.

00:13:58.003 --> 00:13:59.071
Spike.

00:15:22.021 --> 00:15:26.025
Angels that are forced from heaven
have to become demons.

00:15:27.426 --> 00:15:29.428
Isn't that right, Spike?

00:15:32.498 --> 00:15:35.200
I'm only watching a dream
that I never awakened from.

00:15:35.534 --> 00:15:37.670
I'll wake you up right now.

00:15:37.937 --> 00:15:39.204
Don't be so anxious, Vicious.

00:15:39.571 --> 00:15:41.974
It's our first meeting in a while, right?

00:15:42.041 --> 00:15:43.175
A plea for your life?

00:15:43.575 --> 00:15:44.576
Hardly.

00:15:45.177 --> 00:15:48.180
Something like that doesn't
work on you, remember?

00:15:48.948 --> 00:15:52.151
After all, you even kill those
who've saved your life.

00:15:52.718 --> 00:15:57.289
He was a beast who lost his fangs.
That's why he's dead.

00:15:58.724 --> 00:16:00.159
The same goes for you.

00:16:06.465 --> 00:16:09.168
Now, we want you to drop your gun.

00:16:14.606 --> 00:16:17.076
What's wrong? If you don't hurry...

00:16:38.731 --> 00:16:40.099
Are you trying to kill me?

00:17:10.162 --> 00:17:12.364
Oh, man, what the hell have I done?

00:17:17.302 --> 00:17:18.237
Yeah?

00:17:18.470 --> 00:17:20.506
<i>Thank God. Jet? Spike is--</i>

00:17:20.572 --> 00:17:21.473
Not my problem!

00:17:29.515 --> 00:17:30.582
Goddamn it.

00:17:53.739 --> 00:17:55.140
Spike.

00:17:55.207 --> 00:17:58.277
Do you know what your face
looks like right now?

00:17:59.311 --> 00:18:00.279
What?

00:18:00.345 --> 00:18:04.383
The same blood runs in you and me.

00:18:04.450 --> 00:18:08.387
The blood of a beast who wanders,
desiring the blood of others.

00:18:09.421 --> 00:18:12.257
I've bled all of that blood away.

00:18:12.624 --> 00:18:15.094
Then why are you still alive?!

00:20:37.769 --> 00:20:39.338
Just like that,

00:20:39.905 --> 00:20:40.872
sing for me.

00:21:03.595 --> 00:21:06.965
Oh, you're finally up. You've slept
too much. It's been three days.

00:21:10.402 --> 00:21:14.606
What? I was worried about you.
You have to be thankful to me.

00:21:28.920 --> 00:21:29.821
Tone-deaf.

00:21:43.402 --> 00:21:44.703
Oh, well.

00:23:31.676 --> 00:23:35.113
<i>-What a tough world we live in nowadays.</i>
<i>-What are you talking about?</i>

00:23:35.180 --> 00:23:38.183
<i>This guy. They're trying to put</i>
<i>a lid on something that stinks.</i>

00:23:38.450 --> 00:23:39.584
<i>Can we let things go on?</i>

00:23:39.651 --> 00:23:41.686
<i>I'm asking you,</i>
<i>what are you talking about?</i>

00:23:41.753 --> 00:23:43.555
<i>World affairs, man. World affairs.</i>

00:23:43.622 --> 00:23:46.758
<i>With all these lids about,</i>
<i>the world will be buried in lids.</i>

00:23:46.825 --> 00:23:47.993
<i>I don't really get it.</i>

00:23:48.059 --> 00:23:50.128
<i>With stuff like that,</i>
<i>you can't see the truth.</i>

00:23:50.195 --> 00:23:51.663
<i>Truth, huh?</i>

00:23:51.730 --> 00:23:54.065
<i>So, lids like that,</i>
<i>I'll crush them all away.</i>

00:23:54.800 --> 00:23:57.135
<i>Next Episode: "Sympathy for the Devil."</i>

00:23:57.202 --> 00:23:58.670
<i>That sounds smelly.</i>

